<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<section xml:lang="en" xml:id="element-note"
	xmlns="http://purl.oclc.org/NET/dml/1.0"
	xmlns:cdml="http://purl.oclc.org/NET/cdml/1.0"
	xmlns:dct="http://purl.org/dc/terms/">

	<title>The <cdml:node role="element">note</cdml:node> element</title>
	<metadata>
		<list>
			<item property="dct:description">A note or annotation in a document.</item>
		</list>
	</metadata>
	<p>The <cdml:node role="element">note</cdml:node> element represents a generic document note or annotation. It <em>may</em> be used as a root element in <em status="review">DML islands</em> in non-DML documents.</p>
	<list>
		<item>
			<title>Status</title>
			<p>Draft</p>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Flow</title>
			<p href="#block-flow">Block</p>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Children</title>
			<cdml:code language="dml-xpath">
( ( /title?, $block[not( /title | /note )]+ ) | ( $inline | text() )+ )
			</cdml:code>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Attributes</title>
			<cdml:code language="dml-xpath">
( $core.attrs* | $meta.attrs* | @role? )
			</cdml:code>
		</item>
		<item>
			<title>Parents</title>
			<cdml:code language="dml-xpath">
( /dml | /object[parent::$block] | /section )
( /dml | $block[$block[not( self::/note )]] )
			</cdml:code>
		</item>
	</list>

		<p status="review">The <cdml:node role="attribute">role</cdml:node> attribute may be used to provide a form to refine the <cdml:node role="element">note</cdml:node> element meaning. Allowed values are:</p>
		<list>
			<item>
				<title><cdml:value>tip</cdml:value></title>
				<p>A suggestion, tip or trick.</p>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title><cdml:value>warning</cdml:value></title>
				<p>An admonition note.</p>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title><cdml:value>sidebar</cdml:value></title>
				<p>A note that is isolated from the main narrative flow.</p>
				<p status="draft">/section[@role="aside"] or /note[@role="aside"] or @role="sidebar" â€¦?</p>
			</item>
			<item>
				<title><cdml:value>footnote</cdml:value></title>
				<p>A footnote. Footnotes in paged medias usually occur at the end of the page which cite it.</p>
			</item>
		</list>


